During a press briefing, White House Press Secretary Karine Jean-Pierre provided updates on the government's response to Hurricane Idalia and other extreme weather events. She emphasized that the administration is committed to supporting impacted communities and has directed a whole-of-government response. The Federal Emergency Management Agency (FEMA) is on the ground in Florida conducting damage assessments, and President Biden will visit the impacted areas on Saturday. Jean-Pierre also discussed the state of the U.S. electrical grid and the administration's efforts to invest in grid resilience. Additionally, she addressed questions about the President's upcoming trips to Southeast Asia, immigration policy, and the COVID-19 pandemic.